{{Infobox company | name = Hopin Academy | type = for-profit [[private company]] | genre = private educational organization in the developing world | founders = MacCarthy M. Mac-Gbathy and Anders Midtgaard | founded = 2010<ref name=about/> | area_served = [[Ghana]] | homepage = {{URL|www.hopinacademy.org}} }}
'''Hopin Academy''' is a for-profit educational organization based in [[Tamale, Ghana|Tamale]], [[Ghana]] that is open to anyone. Open 24 hours a day, Hopin Academy derives its name from its educational philosophy as a school designed for students to “hop in and hop out," rather than having strictly organized timetable structures.<ref name=Hopin>{{Cite web|title = Hopin Academy|url = http://hopinacademy.org/|website = hopinacademy.org|accessdate = 2015-12-03}}</ref> The school specializes in training in online marketing, social media communication, writing, video production, entrepreneurial work and web communications.<ref name=Hopin /> Hopin Academy has established an international academic partnership with [[Bryn Mawr College]] and [[Haverford College]] through the BiCo-Dalun Summer Action Research Fellowship, a learning program fostered in 2010 where Bryn Mawr and Haverford students create community projects with Ghanaian partners.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Dalun Community Partners {{!}} Dalun-BiCo Lagim Tehi Tuma|url = http://lagim.blogs.brynmawr.edu/category/dalun-community-partners/|website = lagim.blogs.brynmawr.edu|accessdate = 2015-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Bryn Mawr College: Bryn Mawr / Haverford Education Program|url = http://www.brynmawr.edu/education/fieldwork.html|website = www.brynmawr.edu|accessdate = 2015-12-03|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160105131000/http://www.brynmawr.edu/education/fieldwork.html|archivedate = 2016-01-05|df = }}</ref> According to the Hopin Academy website, Hopin Academy offers courses in writing, design, film, and entrepreneurial work.<ref name=about>{{Cite web |title = About us - Hopin Academy |url = http://hopinacademy.org/about.html |website = hopinacademy.org |accessdate = 2015-12-03 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160121002929/http://hopinacademy.org/about.html |archivedate = 2016-01-21 |df = }}</ref> Hopin Academy also provides training to NGOs, government organizations, and other schools, such as the Olive School of Journalism.<ref>{{Cite web|title = OLIVE STUDENTS TO BE TRAINED IN WEB DESIGN AND SOCIAL MEDIA|url = http://www.osjournalism.com/olive-students-to-be-trained-in-web-design-and-social-media/|website = www.osjournalism.com|accessdate = 2015-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Olive School Of Journalism : News And Events|url = http://olivestudents.blogspot.com/p/news-and-events.html|website = olivestudents.blogspot.com|accessdate = 2015-12-03}}</ref>
==History== Hopin Academy was started in 2010 as a social enterprise that aimed to be an alternative to the Ghanaian public education system.<ref>{{Cite web|title = 10 Under 35 Changemakers in Ghana You Need to Know.|url = https://emeritusky.wordpress.com/2013/12/16/10-under-35-changemakers-in-ghana-you-need-to-know/|website = emeritusky|accessdate = 2015-12-06}}</ref> The educational initiative was co-founded by a Ghanaian entrepreneur, MacCarthy M. Mac-Gbathy and the Danish film maker and Harvard-trained "innovator," [[Anders Midtgaard]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = The Future Awards Africa 2015 Nominees Profiles - Page 3 of 9 - The Future Awards Africa|url = http://thefutureafrica.com/awards/tfaa-2015-nominees-profiles/3/|website = The Future Awards Africa|accessdate = 2015-12-03|language = en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Anders Midtgaard {{!}} Hopin Academy {{!}} ZoomInfo.com|url = http://www.zoominfo.com/p/Anders-Midtgaard/-1907006004|website = ZoomInfo|accessdate = 2015-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = 10 Under 35 Changemakers in Ghana You Need to Know.|url = https://emeritusky.wordpress.com/2013/12/16/10-under-35-changemakers-in-ghana-you-need-to-know/|website = emeritusky|accessdate = 2015-12-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Meet the FoDB Team {{!}} Dizem Bella|url = http://www.dizembella.org/content/meet-fodb-team|website = www.dizembella.org|accessdate = 2015-12-03|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151210195852/http://www.dizembella.org/content/meet-fodb-team|archivedate = 2015-12-10|df = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = 10 Under 35. Changemakers In Ghana - TheNewAfrica|url = http://www.thenewafrica.info/10-changemakers-35/|website = TheNewAfrica|accessdate = 2015-12-06|language = en-US|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151208232224/http://www.thenewafrica.info/10-changemakers-35/|archivedate = 2015-12-08|df = }}</ref>
==Collaborations== In addition to offering courses and technological resources, Hopin Academy supports Barcamp Tamale, which is a networking forum hosted in Tamale that connects Ghanaian leaders and innovators with young people.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Barcamp Tamale 2015 Comes Off August 15th|url = https://www.modernghana.com/news/636409/1/barcamp-tamale-2015-comes-off-august-15th.html|website = Modern Ghana |accessdate = 2015-12-03|language = en-GB}}</ref> Hopin Academy also supports the Youth Speak Up Project, which is a Ghanaian advocacy program that aims to empower youth through technology education.<ref>{{Cite web|title = The Youth Speak Up Project {{!}} Youth Empowerment for Life|url = http://www.yefl-ghana.org/news/youth-speak-up-project|website = www.yefl-ghana.org|accessdate = 2015-12-06|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20151210222656/http://www.yefl-ghana.org/news/youth-speak-up-project|archivedate = 2015-12-10|df = }}</ref> Hopin Academy has collaborated with other educational institutions in the international community, including: * [[Young Engineers / Future Leaders|YEFL]] * Olive School of Journalism * [[Tamale Polytechnic]] * University of Development Studies * [[Bryn Mawr College]] * [[Haverford College]] *[[Viborg, Denmark|Viborg]] Gymnasium * Ghana Friendship Groups * [[Copenhagen Business Academy]]<ref name=Hopin />
